I see you want to flatten an array to 1-D. Here is recursive iterator class you can use,

```
$arr = [[&quot;4|1&quot;,&quot;4|3&quot;,&quot;4|6&quot;],[[&quot;4|1|2&quot;,&quot;4|1|8&quot;],[&quot;4|3|4&quot;,&quot;4|3|9&quot;],[&quot;4|6|5&quot;,&quot;4|6|12&quot;]]];
$iterator = new \RecursiveIteratorIterator(new \RecursiveArrayIterator($arr));
$result = [];
foreach($iterator as $v) {
  $result[] = $v;
}
print_r($result);
```

[RecursiveArrayIterator][1] - This iterator allows to unset and modify values and keys while iterating over Arrays and Objects in the same way as the [ArrayIterator][2]. Additionally, it is possible to iterate over the current iterator entry.

[Ref][3].

[Demo][4]

**Solution 2:-**
```
$arr = [[&quot;4|1&quot;,&quot;4|3&quot;,&quot;4|6&quot;],[[&quot;4|1|2&quot;,&quot;4|1|8&quot;],[&quot;4|3|4&quot;,&quot;4|3|9&quot;],[&quot;4|6|5&quot;,&quot;4|6|12&quot;]]];
array_walk_recursive($arr, function($v) use(&amp;$result){
  $result[] = $v;
});
print_r($result);
```

